    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-16T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="1067"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1067">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4089: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-16T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 16, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>185. Referring to the Department’s telegram 171, October 15, the budget was
                    approved yesterday and salary discounting began today.</p>
                <p>By the inclusion of additional revenues and the imposition of a 5 percent
                    reduction in the salaries of the enlisted personnel of the Garde it was possible
                    to reduce the general budget reduction from 25 to 20 percent. A budget reduction
                    of 10 percent will continue to be imposed on the officers and employees of the
                    Office of the Fiscal Representative. Approval of the budget of the Internal
                    Revenue Service required by article X of the 1933 Accord has been deferred for a
                    few days at the request of the Minister of Finance pending further consideration
                    of what would be an expedient rate of budget reduction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
